1
00:00:00,584 --> 00:00:01,667
In the summer there was...

2
00:00:01,834 --> 00:00:03,918
Just as our Muslim neighbors taught us the Quran

3
00:00:04,417 --> 00:00:05,626
They also had in summer

4
00:00:05,876 --> 00:00:08,000
Their children came to learn the Gospel

5
00:00:08,959 --> 00:00:11,083
They taught them the Gospel and we joined them

6
00:00:11,125 --> 00:00:13,334
Interviewer: In what place did this happen?

7
00:00:13,375 --> 00:00:15,375
Witness: It was during the summer vacation

8
00:00:15,375 --> 00:00:16,667
When there were no schools

9
00:00:16,959 --> 00:00:20,042
They came from 10 in the morning

10
00:00:20,292 --> 00:00:22,334
Until 12 noon, for two hours

11
00:00:22,876 --> 00:00:23,876
They had this ritual

12
00:00:24,125 --> 00:00:26,959
They taught them the Gospel in the churches

13
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:30,459
In the churches themselves, all churches opened on these days

14
00:00:30,751 --> 00:00:33,042
They taught them the Gospel in the summer vacation

15
00:00:33,876 --> 00:00:38,459
Interviewer: Were the ones leading these rituals priests?

16
00:00:39,334 --> 00:00:42,000
The church choir? Relatives? Who were they?

17
00:00:42,042 --> 00:00:44,667
Witness: All the neighborhoods, the same area

18
00:00:44,709 --> 00:00:47,459
Just as they had school study

19
00:00:47,751 --> 00:00:50,667
They had a summer ritual, going to study the Gospel

20
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:53,375
And there was crowding like at school

21
00:00:53,375 --> 00:00:55,542
There was recess and they went out to the church

22
00:00:55,834 --> 00:00:58,751
And they brought them cake and chocolate

23
00:00:58,918 --> 00:01:02,626
After every half hour they had a 10 minute break

24
00:01:03,042 --> 00:01:04,459
Like recess in school

25
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,250
Also you had a recess after every half hour

26
00:01:06,626 --> 00:01:08,709
They had this thing in the church

27
00:01:08,751 --> 00:01:10,667
They taught the Gospel

28
00:01:10,959 --> 00:01:13,500
To children and schools during the summer vacation

29
00:01:13,751 --> 00:01:16,584
Interviewer: I want you to describe the place

30
00:01:16,626 --> 00:01:19,334
When you used to come to it

31
00:01:19,626 --> 00:01:21,042
You have memories there

32
00:01:21,042 --> 00:01:24,083
What did you remember when you came to this place?

33
00:01:24,125 --> 00:01:26,959
What do you remember was in this place?

34
00:01:27,042 --> 00:01:31,250
Can you describe for us the furniture in each room?

35
00:01:31,626 --> 00:01:34,792
I hope you go back in your memories a little and describe it to us

36
00:01:35,751 --> 00:01:37,417
Witness: This church

37
00:01:37,751 --> 00:01:39,459
We are now talking about the Armenian Church

38
00:01:40,250 --> 00:01:41,626
I enter from this door

39
00:01:42,209 --> 00:01:44,209
The cleanliness was indescribable

40
00:01:44,834 --> 00:01:46,125
And the appearance was indescribable

41
00:01:46,209 --> 00:01:48,667
You entered and they had chairs

42
00:01:48,709 --> 00:01:51,042
Arranged neatly, the chair was like a couch

43
00:01:51,709 --> 00:01:55,042
We called it a couch but it was thinner than a couch

44
00:01:55,417 --> 00:01:56,417
They were in rows

45
00:01:56,459 --> 00:02:00,209
One, two, up to about 20 couches

46
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:02,042
People sat on them

47
00:02:02,417 --> 00:02:04,209
And this was the entrance passage

48
00:02:04,417 --> 00:02:07,209
And on the opposite side also couches

49
00:02:07,626 --> 00:02:08,751
We entered and sat

50
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,584
It was indescribable with the lights

51
00:02:11,918 --> 00:02:13,375
This proof, these chandeliers

52
00:02:13,709 --> 00:02:16,292
These chandeliers, this chandelier and that

53
00:02:16,584 --> 00:02:18,542
This was their dome

54
00:02:18,792 --> 00:02:21,209
You had the pulpit above

55
00:02:21,459 --> 00:02:23,584
This was where the priest went up

56
00:02:23,792 --> 00:02:24,918
He gave a sermon from it

57
00:02:25,083 --> 00:02:26,876
Sometimes, there was no space here

58
00:02:27,167 --> 00:02:28,209
He went up

59
00:02:28,459 --> 00:02:30,042
To speak to the women

60
00:02:31,250 --> 00:02:35,459
The saint and the priest both went up and spoke from this pulpit when there was crowding

61
00:02:35,959 --> 00:02:38,751
He came out here, they stood there, and he raised his voice so they heard him

62
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:42,709
Like our sermon pulpit

63
00:02:42,918 --> 00:02:44,042
This was their pulpit

64
00:02:44,626 --> 00:02:47,500
These chandeliers lit in an indescribable way

65
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:50,542
And always chocolate was their symbol

66
00:02:50,834 --> 00:02:52,042
Chocolate was a symbol for them

67
00:02:52,334 --> 00:02:55,083
And they had candy they called sweet and sour, with a mint flavor

68
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:57,792
Mint like what we used to call alouja before

69
00:02:58,125 --> 00:02:59,959
This was their type of mint

70
00:03:00,417 --> 00:03:02,584
They offered it as a blessing to the children

71
00:03:02,834 --> 00:03:04,459
They purified them and brought them close

72
00:03:04,751 --> 00:03:06,334
And put the chocolate here

73
00:03:06,417 --> 00:03:07,667
There was no one

74
00:03:08,292 --> 00:03:13,083
Who entered this place

75
00:03:13,751 --> 00:03:16,209
When you entered, before sitting down

76
00:03:16,584 --> 00:03:18,500
You came and took a piece of chocolate and ate it

77
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,250
Then you sat there

78
00:03:20,459 --> 00:03:22,042
They welcomed you with a beautiful spirit

79
00:03:22,083 --> 00:03:24,584
It was a church, I do not know how to describe it to you

80
00:03:24,834 --> 00:03:26,792
Beautiful and painful memories

81
00:03:27,125 --> 00:03:29,083
So many, I cannot remember them all because of their number

82
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:31,584
As many as they were, I feel sorrow
